<paragraph id="7B7436B2FFD9FFED52AEE093FBDCFF73" blockId="6.[151,1437,1691,2004]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">
Harold (1869) described the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC5026E094FD78F912" box="[543,672,1692,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC5026E094FD78F912" box="[543,672,1692,1716]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Byrrhidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC50E6E094FBE5F912" authority="Harold, 1869" authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1869" box="[735,1085,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovale">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC50E6E094FC7BF912" box="[735,931,1692,1716]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Byrrhidium ovale</emphasis>
Harold, 1869
</taxonomicName>
as the only constituent species. The very doubtful 
<typeStatus id="A4708810FFD9FFEC5353E0C8FE42F97E" box="[362,410,1728,1752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">type</typeStatus>
locality was cited as “Port. Natal” by Harold (1869) although the label reads only “Natal”. 
<bibRefCitation id="1F5A4B43FFD9FFEC52AEE0EBFEF6F95A" author="Kolbe" box="[151,302,1763,1788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" refString="Kolbe, H. J. (1908) Dynastidae, Cetoniidae und Scarabaeidae. Schultze L.: Zoologische und Arthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika. Bd. 1. Denkschrift Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 13, 121 - 132." type="journal article" year="1908">Kolbe (1908)</bibRefCitation>
later described a new genus and species, 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC5133E0ECFB7AF95A" authority="Kolbe 1908" authorityName="Kolbe" authorityYear="1908" box="[778,1186,1763,1788]" genus="Elassocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC5133E0ECFBCDF95A" box="[778,1045,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Elassocanthon brevipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1F5A4B43FFD9FFEC5624E0EBFB7AF95A" author="Kolbe" box="[1053,1186,1763,1788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" refString="Kolbe, H. J. (1908) Dynastidae, Cetoniidae und Scarabaeidae. Schultze L.: Zoologische und Arthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika. Bd. 1. Denkschrift Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 13, 121 - 132." type="journal article" year="1908">Kolbe 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see figure 3B, E and H) from Brit. S.W. Africa, Kl. Namaland, Kamaggas [=Komaggas 
<geoCoordinate id="1EFF5075FFD9FFEC51A0E100FC2BF886" box="[921,1011,1800,1824]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" precision="555" value="-29.8">S29.80°</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="1EFF5075FFD9FFEC51C4E10FFB85F886" box="[1021,1117,1799,1824]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" precision="555" value="17.5">E17.50°</geoCoordinate>
], vii. [19]04, L. Schultze S. This locality is consistent with the travels of L. Schultze during 
<date id="0F751072FFD9FFEC51AAE124FBFFF8E2" box="[915,1063,1836,1860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" value="1904-08">August 1904</date>
from Steinkopf to Port Nolloth [
<geoCoordinate id="1EFF5075FFD9FFEC52A4E147FF22F8CE" box="[157,250,1871,1896]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" precision="555" value="-29.26">S29.26°</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="1EFF5075FFD9FFEC533AE147FEBBF8CE" box="[259,355,1871,1896]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" precision="555" value="16.87">E16.87°</geoCoordinate>
], Henkries [
<geoCoordinate id="1EFF5075FFD9FFEC53D4E158FD91F8CE" box="[493,585,1872,1896]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" precision="555" value="-28.97">S28.97°</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="1EFF5075FFD9FFEC506AE158FD69F8CE" box="[595,689,1872,1896]" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" precision="555" value="18.09">E18.09°</geoCoordinate>
] and Ka[o]maggas (
<bibRefCitation id="1F5A4B43FFD9FFEC51A2E147FB9AF8CE" author="Schultze" box="[923,1090,1871,1896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" refString="Schultze, L (1908) Zoologische und anthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika: ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1903 - 1905. Erster Band, Systematik und Tiergeographie / mit Unterstutzung der Kgl. Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin, 1 e Lieferung. Jena, Fischer, 646 pp." type="book chapter" year="1908">Schultze 1908</bibRefCitation>
). In 1938, Janssens noted that 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC52AEE17CFDE9F82A" authority="Kolbe, 1908" authorityName="Kolbe" authorityYear="1908" box="[151,561,1907,1932]" genus="Elassocanthon" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC52AEE17CFE79F82A" box="[151,417,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Elassocanthon brevipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1F5A4B43FFD9FFEC539EE17BFDE9F82A" author="Kolbe" box="[423,561,1907,1932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" refString="Kolbe, H. J. (1908) Dynastidae, Cetoniidae und Scarabaeidae. Schultze L.: Zoologische und Arthropologische Ergebnisse einer Forschungsreise im westlichen und zentralen Sudafrika. Bd. 1. Denkschrift Medizinisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft zu Jena, 13, 121 - 132." type="journal article" year="1908">Kolbe, 1908</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is most likely a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC514DE17CFBE1F82A" box="[884,1081,1908,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovale">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC514DE17CFBE1F82A" box="[884,1081,1908,1932]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Byrrhidium ovale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However the two species were only formally synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation id="1F5A4B43FFD9FFEC5034E19FFC83F816" author="Scholtz" box="[525,859,1943,1968]" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" refString="Scholtz, C. H. &amp; Howden, H. F. (1987) A revision of the southern African Cathonina [sic] (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Journal of the Entomological Society of Southern Africa, 50, 75 - 119." type="journal article" year="1987">Scholtz and Howden (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, who also added two new species to the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC52AEE1B4FE4CF875" box="[151,404,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexum">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC52AEE1B4FE4CF875" box="[151,404,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Byrrhidium convexum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD9FFEC53ECE1B4FD36F875" box="[469,750,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="namaquense">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD9FFEC53ECE1B4FD36F875" box="[469,750,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="496">Byrrhidium namaquense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, following the reasoning in 
<tableCitation id="36490309FFD9FFEC5687E1B3FACFF872" box="[1214,1303,1979,2004]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[151,239,833,856]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,916,1143]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 1. Table showing the differences between Elassocanthon brevipes and Byrrhidium namaquense according to Scholtz and Howden 1987 with characters for Byrrhidium ovale included from images of the holotype." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2FB4663AFFD7FFE252AEE549FB07FCDE" pageId="6" pageNumber="496" tableUuid="2FB4663AFFD7FFE252AEE549FB07FCDE">Table 1</tableCitation>
, where we compared images of the three 
<typeStatus id="A4708810FFD8FFED53DEE690FDCFFF16" box="[487,535,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">type</typeStatus>
specimens, we are of the opinion that 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD8FFED51FAE690FB0EFF16" box="[963,1238,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="namaquense" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD8FFED51FAE690FB0EFF16" box="[963,1238,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">Byrrhidium namaquense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="528C57DBFFD8FFED56E4E690FAFEFF09" box="[1245,1318,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="BCCB4D31FFD8FFED531AE6B4FE3FFF72" box="[291,487,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Byrrhidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovale">
<emphasis id="49BFEAA0FFD8FFED531AE6B4FE3FFF72" box="[291,487,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="497">Byrrhidium ovale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, we synonymize the two species.
</paragraph>
